HEADWORD: Water sail
<hw>Wa"ter sail`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A small sail
sometimes set under a studding sail or under a driver boom, and reaching
nearly to the water.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

